news.title: Kolkata civic body identifies 150 'extremely vulnerable' buildings for demolition
news.para: A communication in this regard has reached the KMC borough executive engineers from the civic headquarters, asking them to take immediate action to raze rickety buildings that might collapse in the event of incessant rain.

news.title: Chennai: 196 buildings on Mandaveli-Adyar metro route could be affected
news.para: A metro rail official said a survey had identified 119 such buildings between Mandaveli and Greenways Road, and 77 buildings between Greenways Road and Adyar junction.

news.title: Lucknow: Deposit house tax with 10% discount till August 31
news.para: The decision was taken by mayor Sanyukta Bhatia after witnessing heavy rush on LMC counters to take advantage of the discount on the last day on Sunday.

news.title: Complete housing programme on time: Andhra Pradesh CM
news.para: The officials told the chief minister that the construction work of houses in Visakhapatnam would start by the end of October 2022. They said that the tendering and other process has been completed here and the work is ready to start.

news.title: SC dismisses PIL seeking alternative solution to Supertech twin towers' demolition
news.para: ​A bench of Justices DY Chandrachud and Sudhanshu Dhulia also imposed a fine of Rs 5 lakh on the NGO 'Centre for Law and Good Governance' and directed that the cost be deposited in the registry to be utilised for the benefit of the family members of lawyers who were affected by Covid.

news.title: Noida: 'Charging' of Supertech twin towers on hold as CBRI studies reports
news.para: Edifice Engineering, the company in charge of the demolition, is waiting for clearances from the Central Building Research Institute (CBRI), which has asked for details of the blast design, explosives to be used, ground vibration and safety measures.

news.title: China banks may face $350 billion in losses from property crisis
news.para: A spiraling crisis of stalled projects has dented the confidence of hundreds of thousands of homebuyers, triggering a mortgage boycott across more than 90 cities and warnings of broader systemic risks. The big question now is not if, but how much it will batter the nation’s $56 trillion banking system.

news.title: Oaktree, Hines may buy GM Infinity's Bengaluru property
news.para: The property is proposed to have a commercial real estate development potential of more than 3 million sq ft along Bengaluru's Sarjapur Road.

news.title: Investors' money of over Rs 1.12 lakh crore stuck in various Sahara group entities: Minister
news.para: Chaudhary said Rs 19,400.87 crore belonging to 2.33 crore investors is stuck in Sahara Indian Real Estate Corporation Ltd (SIRECL), Rs 6,380.50 crore (75 lakh investors) in Sahara Housing Investment Corporation Ltd (SHICL) and Rs 47,245 crore (4 crore investors) in Sahara Credit Cooperative Society Ltd.

news.title: DDA facing cash deficit of Rs 9,600 crore due to high unsold inventory of flats
news.para: The revelation comes barely weeks after Delhi Lt Governor V K Saxena tweeted that while the DDA is owner of one of the costliest and largest chunks of real estate in the world, “mismanagement” has led to its liabilities exceeding Rs 10,000 crore.

news.title: Kansai Nerolac Paints' net profit up 36.5% to Rs 152 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: Its revenue from operations rose 46.23 per cent to Rs 2,051.37 crore from Rs 1,402.76 crore in the year-ago quarter. Total expenses were at Rs 1,847.95 crore, 46.59 per cent higher than Rs 1,260.62 crore in Q1 FY22.

news.title: Telangana: Sahiti Infratec buyers lodge complaint, MD vows to chalk out solution
news.para: They further complained that despite having deposited a huge amount of funds with the company, the company kept on missing the project execution, as well as refund deadlines.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Red Apple Residency director, bank officials booked in Rs 200 crore fraud case
news.para: Rajkumar Jain, the director of Red Apple Residency in Raj Nagar Extension, and some of his family members were arrested in Delhi on March 1.

news.title: Mumbai: Prestige Estates to complete Shivshahi society redevelopment project
news.para: Eight years after they vacated their buildings, society members on Sunday unanimously decided to appoint Bengaluru-based developer Prestige Estates to complete the work.

news.title: HC restrains ED from taking coercive steps against Piramal Realty assets
news.para: ED has alleged that Omkar Group took a Rs 410 crore loan from Yes Bank to construct buildings for slum dwellers under the Slum Rehabilitation Authority (SRA) scheme at Wadala (in Mumbai) but redirected the money to other companies.
